net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.template

Class TemplateContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.template.TemplateContainer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource, Component, ParentComponent
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TemplateCompositeValueEditor

    public class TemplateContainer
extends ComponentImpl
implements ParentComponent
    Container component that contains other components.

    The children of this container can be organized via a XML template.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@venturetech.net)

      • TemplateContainer

        public TemplateContainer(TemplateDataSource templateDataSource)
        Create a new TemplateContainer.

        Make sure to call applyTemplate() when done configuring this container.

        Parameters:
        templateDataSource - the template data source. This should be configured to point to a unique file for this template container.

      • applyTemplate

        public void applyTemplate()
        Apply the template defined by the TemplateDataSource if there is one. This must be called once prior to this component being rendered. If the template has not been created yet, then the components are rendered in the order defined by the code.

      • getHTMLElement

        public HTMLElement getHTMLElement()
        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.

        Specified by:
        getHTMLElement in interface Component
        Returns:
        the element.
